Package com.example.superior_intelligence

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.example.superior_intelligence.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Event extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a mood event that a user can create, store, and retrieve from Firestore. Includes properties like title, date, overlay color, mood, and situation.

      overlayColor - The color overlay associated with the event.
      imageUrl - The URL of the image associated with the event.
      emojiResource - The emoji resource ID for the mood.
      isFollowed - Whether the event is followed by the user.
      isMyPost - Whether the event was created by the user.25
      postUser - The username of the event creator.
      public_status - True if the post is public, otherwise private.

    • Event

      public Event(String id, String title, String date, String overlayColor, String imageUrl, int emojiResource, boolean isFollowed, boolean isMyPost, String mood, String moodExplanation, String situation, String postUser, Double lat, Double lng, boolean public_status)
      Constructor for creating an event with additional mood and situation details.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique ID for mood events.
      title - The title of the event.
      date - The date of the event as a String.
      overlayColor - The color overlay associated with the event.
      imageUrl - The URL of the image associated with the event.
      emojiResource - The emoji resource ID for the mood.
      isFollowed - Whether the event is followed by the user.
      isMyPost - Whether the event was created by the user.
      mood - The mood associated with the event.
      moodExplanation - The explanation for the mood.
      situation - The social situation during the event.
      postUser - The username of the event creator.
      public_status - Post status, true if post is public, false otherwise
